---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../config';
---

<Layout title="About">
  <div class="about-page">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>About My ESPHome Workshop</h1>
      <p class="hero-description">
        Welcome to my personal documentation site where I track my journey 
        turning a collection of dev boards and sensors into (maybe) useful smart home devices.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-grid">
      <!-- Site Purpose -->
      <section class="card">
        <h2>Why This Site Exists</h2>
        <p>
          After 15+ years of accumulating microcontrollers, sensors, and random gadgets, 
          I decided it was time to actually use them. This site serves as my workshop 
          documentation‚Äîtracking what I have, what I've built, and what I've learned 
          along the way.
        </p>
        <p>
          After all these years I realized that it wasn't me going for the new shiny thing, it was
          just that the world wasn't ready! Now that we have great projects like <a href="https://esphome.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ESPHome</a> and 
          <a href="https://www.home-assistant.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Home Assistant</a>, 
          it's finally time to take over the <strike>world</strike> home.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- How to Use This Site -->
      <section class="card">
        <h2>How to Use This Site</h2>
        <div class="usage-section">
          <h3>üîå Devices</h3>
          <p>
            Browse all the hardware in my collection. Each device includes wiring 
            diagrams, example code, and my personal notes about using it. Well ... that's the plan at least.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="usage-section">
          <h3>üõ†Ô∏è Projects</h3>
          <p>
            Complete project builds with full documentation. Shows what devices 
            were used, the motivation behind the project, and how it turned out.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="usage-section">
          <h3>üß© Components</h3>
          <p>
            ESPHome software components and integrations. These are the building 
            blocks that make the hardware work. Just notes and tying components together.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="usage-section">
          <h3>üìì Notes</h3>
          <p>
            General knowledge, setup guides, troubleshooting tips, and lessons 
            learned. The stuff that doesn't fit neatly into device or project docs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Device Status Guide -->
      <section class="card">
        <h2>Understanding Device Statuses</h2>
        <p>Every device has a status that shows how I'm currently using it:</p>
        <div class="status-guide">
          <div class="status-row">
            <span class="status-badge ready">üì¶ Ready</span>
            <span class="status-description">Tested, working, ready to use ... but not used just yet</span>
          </div>
          <div class="status-row">
            <span class="status-badge testing">üß™ Testing</span>
            <span class="status-description">Currently experimenting with this on my bench. Updating documentation as I go along.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="status-row">
            <span class="status-badge deployed">‚úÖ Deployed</span>
            <span class="status-description">Actively used in a working project - contains a link to the project where it is used.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="status-row">
            <span class="status-badge pending">üî¶ Pending</span>
            <span class="status-description">Documentation incomplete, waiting to start testing it. NOTE that documentation might not be fully correct until I finish testing.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="status-row">
            <span class="status-badge unsupported">‚ùï Unsupported</span>
            <span class="status-description">Doesn't work with ESPHome - for now üòâ</span>
          </div>
          <div class="status-row">
            <span class="status-badge retired">‚è∏Ô∏è Retired</span>
            <span class="status-description">Was deployed but no longer in use</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Project Status Guide -->
      <section class="card">
        <h2>Understanding Project Statuses</h2>
        <p>Projects are tracked through their lifecycle:</p>
        <div class="status-guide">
          <div class="status-row">
            <span class="status-badge idea">üí≠ Idea</span>
            <span class="status-description">Concept stage, planning and gathering parts</span>
          </div>
          <div class="status-row">
            <span class="status-badge in-progress">üõ†Ô∏è In Progress</span>
            <span class="status-description">Actively building and testing</span>
          </div>
          <div class="status-row">
            <span class="status-badge completed">‚úÖ Completed</span>
            <span class="status-description">Working and deployed in production</span>
          </div>
          <div class="status-row">
            <span class="status-badge abandoned">‚è∏Ô∏è Abandoned</span>
            <span class="status-description">Discontinued (but documented for future reference)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- How to Contribute -->
      <section class="card">
        <h2>How to Contribute</h2>
        <p>
          Found an error? Have a suggestion?
        </p>
        <div class="usage-section">
          <h3>Report an Issue</h3>
          <p>
            Every content page has a "Report an Issue" button that opens a GitHub 
            issue with the page details pre-filled. Use this to report errors, 
            broken links, or outdated information.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="usage-section">
          <h3>Suggest a Feature</h3>
          <p>
            Have an idea for a new feature or improvement? Open a feature request 
            on GitHub with your suggestion.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="contribution-links">
          <a href={`https://github.com/${siteConfig.github.repo}`} class="button" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            View on GitHub ‚Üí
          </a>
          <a href={siteConfig.github.issuesUrl} class="button button-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Open an Issue ‚Üí
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
  }

  .hero {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .hero-description {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .content-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .card {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .card h2 {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
  }

  .card h3 {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .usage-section {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .usage-section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .usage-section h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .status-guide {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .status-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .status-description {
    color: var(--gray);
    flex: 1;
  }

  .contribution-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .button {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .button:hover {
    background: var(--accent-dark);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .button-secondary {
    background: white;
    color: var(--accent);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent);
  }

  .button-secondary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-light);
    border-color: var(--accent-dark);
    color: var(--accent-dark);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .hero-description {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .card {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .status-row {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .contribution-links {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .button {
      text-align: center;
      width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>
